In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 2009 as National Adoption Month. He highlights the importance of providing safe and loving families for all children, and acknowledges that there are thousands of young people in America waiting to be adopted. The president emphasizes the need to reduce the number of children awaiting adoption and to make adoption a viable option for more families. He also addresses the specific needs of children in foster care and calls on federal, state, and local governments, communities, and individuals to provide the necessary resources and support for these children. The president concludes by urging all Americans to observe National Adoption Month by supporting and honoring adoptive families and actively participating in efforts to find permanent homes for waiting children.